ZH: 明天圣诞节降临。 
EN: Tomorrow Christmas will come.

ZH: 夏天的雨水降临了。 
EN: The summer rain has arrived.

ZH: 夜晚的黑暗降临了。 
EN: The darkness of the night has fallen.

ZH: 温暖的春天正在降临。 
EN: The warm spring is approaching.

ZH: 阳光照亮了大地，春天降临了。 
EN: The sunlight illuminated the earth, and spring arrived.

ZH: 十二月即将降临，气温会下降。 
EN: December is about to come, and the temperature will drop.

ZH: 龙卷风突然降临，给城市带来了巨大的破坏。 
EN: The tornado suddenly hit, causing massive destruction to the city.

ZH: 天使降临地球，给人们带来了和平和希望。 
EN: Angels descended to the earth, bringing peace and hope to people.

ZH: 年轻人对技术的热情降临了，他们开始大量使用智能手机。 
EN: The enthusiasm for technology has arrived among young people, and they have started using smartphones extensively.

ZH: 当爱情降临时，你会感到幸福和喜悦。 
EN: When love arrives, you will feel happiness and joy.

ZH: 雨后彩虹降临了，给人们带来了美丽的景色。 
EN: After the rain, a rainbow appeared, bringing beautiful scenery to people.

ZH: 夜空中闪耀着无数的星星，犹如神秘的心灵降临。 
EN: Countless stars shine in the night sky, as if mysterious souls have descended.

ZH: 当你最需要帮助时，好朋友会降临到你身边。 
EN: When you need help the most, good friends will come to your side.

ZH: 激励和鼓舞的话语降临在乏味的生活中。 
EN: Encouraging and inspiring words come into the dull life.

ZH: 新的一年即将降临，我们要准备好迎接新的挑战。 
EN: The new year is approaching, and we must prepare ourselves to embrace new challenges.

ZH: 他一夜之间变得富有，好运降临在他身上。 
EN: He became rich overnight, and good luck came to him.

ZH: 当失望和困惑降临时，你要坚持下去。 
EN: When disappointment and confusion come, you must persevere.

ZH: 春风轻轻吹过，给大地带来了新的活力。 
EN: The spring breeze blows gently, bringing new vitality to the earth.

ZH: 黑夜将至，我们要小心行事。 
EN: Night is approaching, and we need to be careful.

ZH: 好运降临在他身上，他赢得了彩票大奖。 
EN: Good luck came to him, and he won the lottery jackpot.
